Class BlockOption

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.californium.core.coap.BlockOption

  • public final class BlockOption
extends Object
    BlockOption represents a Block1 or Block2 option in a CoAP message.

      • size2Szx

        public static int size2Szx(int blockSize)
        Gets the 3-bit SZX code for a block size as specified by RFC 7959, Section 2.2: 
         16 bytes = 2^4 --> 0
 ... 
 1024 bytes = 2^10 -> 6

        This method is tolerant towards illegal block sizes that are < 16 or > 1024 bytes in that it will return the corresponding codes for sizes 16 or 1024 respectively.

        Parameters:
        blockSize - The block size in bytes.
        Returns:
        The szx code for the largest number of bytes that is less than or equal to the block size.

      • szx2Size

        public static int szx2Size(int szx)
        Gets the number of bytes corresponding to a szx code.

        This method is tolerant towards illegal codes that are < 0 or > 6 in that it will return the corresponding values for codes 0 or 6 respectively.

        Parameters:
        szx - The code.
        Returns:
        The corresponding number of bytes.
